'''Henry Dias Abeygoonewardane''' (29 December 1917 - ) was a Sri Lankan politician and [[member of parliament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.lk/members-of-parliament/directory-of-members/viewMember/2010|title=Hon. Abeygoonewardane, Henry Dias, M.P.|work=Directory of Past Members|publisher=[[Parliament of Sri Lanka]]|accessdate=20 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Members of the Legislatures of Ceylon: 1931-1972|publisher=National State Assembly |date=1972|author=Jātika Rājya Sabhāva Pustakālya|page=4}}</ref>

In 1947, standing as the [[Communist Party of Ceylon|Communist Party]]'s candidate, Abeygoonewardane was elected to the first parliament of Ceylon, representing the [[Matara Electoral District (1947–1989)|Matara electorate]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slelections.gov.lk/web/images/pdf/general-election-results/general-election-1947.pdf|title=Result of Parliamentary General Election 1947|publisher=Department of Elections, Sri Lanka|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> He received over 57% of the vote whilst his nearest rival obtained only 25%.

