'''Xaver Affentranger''' (born 1 December 1897, date of death unknown) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[Cross-country skiing|cross-country skier]], [[Nordic combined]] skier, and [[Ski jumping|ski jumper]] who competed in the 1920s.

At the [[1924 Winter Olympics]] he finished 17th in the [[Nordic combined at the 1924 Winter Olympics|Nordic combined event]], 22nd in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 1924 Winter Olympics – Men's 18 km|18 km cross-country competition]], and 24th in the [[Ski jumping at the 1924 Winter Olympics|ski jumping event]].

He won a bronze medal in the Nordic combined at the [[1925 FIS Nordic World Ski Championships]] in [[Johannisbad]].

